						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the backyard of Gadigeyya Ēṇigimaṭha.</p>						

						<p>Vikramāditya VI (Undated).</p>						

						<p>This worn out inscription refers to the reign of Tribhuvanamalladēva and the date is lost, except Thursday.</p>						

						<p>It refers to the feudatory chief <hi rend="italic">Mahāsāmanta</hi> Aṅka of the Raṭṭa family, Śāntiyakka and the Kūṁḍi province. Describes the Jaina teacher Jinadēva-sūri of the Yāpanīya-saṁgha, Maiḷāpaanvaya and Kāraya-gaṇa, to which Muḷḷa-bhaṭṭāraka and others belonged. Seems to record a gift of land to a Jaina temple.</p>						

						</summary>
